quotedObject.fullText:
Monster trucks and F1: Chronobiology and seasonal clock analogy #346
I explained this to a 12 year old recently
Whenever I feel like I'm repeating myself, people close to me say 'why didn't you say it like that in the first place'
I don't know if I'm explaining things more clearly, whether they're becoming more familiar with the concept and hearing new bits or whether I'm just repeating myself... maybe somewhere between the lot
Imagine you have a racing team, and this team races all over the world, in deserts, snow and mud, from courses that resemble F1 Grand Prix to monster truck like courses
There are several components that make a good team
1. There is a man that finds out what the next race conditions are and decides what tyres, wheels, suspension etc to put on, his name is the 'hypothalamus'
2. There is an admin guy that receives the email on the details of the next race, he is called the 'eye' and his deputy is called the 'skin'
3. There is a man that decides what temperature the cockpit put should be based on the temperature of the race location, his name is 'BAT' or 'brownie' to his mates
4. There is a man who works out how much fuel or energy needs to be stored or used, depending on the length of the race, his name is 'leptin'
5. There is a lorry that carries all of the above, called 'the body'
6. There is the fairly rigid chassis called 'gene' which doesn't ever really change too much if things are normal
7. Then there is the most versatile part of the whole team, the engine, used in all conditions, it's called the mighty 'Mitochondria'
Thing is, it's very easy to see that if the 'eye' gets the wrong email, and the 'hypothalamus' puts on the snow tyres with huge 4x4 height suspension for a race around flat tarmac, you can see there will be no competition, if the team can even finish the race
Likewise we don't want to store too much fuel if we need it for the race, we want to burn it efficiently
The message that comes through, or messages is key. With the wrong information the race is lost
As powerful and as versatile as might 'mito' are, if the eye doesn't get the right race details, the engines are stabbing in th dark... everyone is relying on everyone else
Light, fat and heat are all sending these messages through our eyes and skin all the time, problem is we're blocking up all the inboxes and we're not programming around the seasons... instead, we're only prepared for a small margin of heat, food and light
